choices.text:
…… We all tried four times to peddle our bicycles to the store, but traffic and trucks were just too much of a hazard.

Distance to nearest grocery store: 1 km Hilly, traffic filled roads made this a last resort for grocery shopping

Contract made with the teenage kids: if you drive daddy’s vehicle to the store, we can make a Deal no deal game of full exchange of :"what you or I want to shop for”

Road cycling can be great weather and can be a challenge when there is lots of steady rain.

We cycled on our tandem seats over this spectacular bridge built in 1968 in the Algarve of Portugal.

This is another lift the handle bars up and down as you slowly pedal. There are some really long hauls out there.

Dottret is known for some of the most beautiful mountains in Portugal.

Back to Vilamoura, our stop before Estonia

We are now in Port Hueneme hanging out in our Coffee Shops. (Last year we spent time in Portimao and Vilamoura.) It was a smooth journey to Santa Barbara by Amtrak from Port Hueneme to Pasadena – slept most of the way. Just our luck. We have had intermittent rain and are staying cozy in the coffee shops, reading, writing and working. We head to England in four days.

Love

SiS

By some strange will of fate, we had missed out on going to Singapore on our previous trip to Jakarta
